            <h2>Carry-On (Hand) Baggage</h2>
            <p>You can travel with one or more items on board, depending on the travel class or ticket type, size, and weight limits. For the light-ticket holders, sometimes overhead bin space is limited, and they may be asked at no charge to check hand baggage at the gate. Thus, pack your essentials, such as medicines and valuables, in your smaller bag just in case. </p>
            <h2>Special &amp; Oversized Baggage</h2>
            <p>There is a particular provision for special and oversized items such as sports equipment, musical instruments, wedding dresses, and more. In most cases, you’ll need to reserve space in advance and may pay an extra fee, and the airline offers dedicated provisions for items such as sports gear: skis, bicycles, golf clubs, surfboards, etc. Musical instruments include small instruments in the cabin (subject to space) or hold. </p>
            <h3>Restricted &amp; Prohibited Items</h3>
            <p>Certain items (lithium batteries, sprays, sharp objects) are restricted in both hands and hold baggage. Always consult the “What you cannot bring” section on KLM.com before departure. </p>
            <h3>Lost, Delayed or Damaged Baggage</h3>
