            <h3>Tips for a Smooth Journey</h3>
            <p>You must measure and weigh your bags at home to avoid surprises. Sometimes, people do not weigh and measure their bags, which are overweight or oversized, at the airport. Another tip is to label each piece with your name, phone number, and itinerary. Another tip is to arrive early to allow time for check-in and security. For baggage updates, you can also check “My Trip” 24 hours before departure. </p>
            <h2>FAQs</h2>
            <h3>1. What is the carry-on baggage allowance for KLM Economy Class? </h3>
            <p>Economy passengers can bring one large carry-on bag (55 × 35 × 25 cm) and one small accessory (40 × 30 × 15 cm), with a combined weight of up to 12 kg. </p>
            <h3>2. How much checked baggage can I bring on a KLM Economy Standard ticket? </h3>
            <p>Economy Standard ticket holders can check in one bag weighing up to 23 kg, with dimensions up to 158 cm (length + width + height). </p>
            <h3>3. Are there extra charges for special or oversized baggage with KLM? </h3>
            <p>KLM typically requires reservations and additional fees for special or oversized items such as sports gear, musical instruments, and wedding attire. </p>
            <h3>4. What should I do if KLM loses, delays, or damages my baggage? </h3>
            <p>Immediately report the issue at the airport baggage service desk, or manage your claim and track your baggage status online through KLM’s official portal. </p>
            <h3>5. What items are prohibited in KLM baggage? </h3>
            <p>KLM restricts lithium batteries, aerosols, sharp objects, and other hazardous materials. Always check the complete list on the airline's website before packing. </p>
            <h3>6. Does KLM provide baggage allowance for infants travelling on a lap? </h3>
            <p>Yes, infants travelling on a lap are allowed one carry-on item (55 × 35 × 25 cm, 12 kg max.) and one checked bag weighing up to 10 kg (158 cm dimensions). </p>
            <h3>7. How can I ensure a smooth baggage check-in with KLM? </h3>
            <p>To avoid issues at check-in, weigh and measure your bags in advance, label them with your contact information, and arrive early for your flight. You can verify baggage details through the “My Trip” section on KLM’s website 24 hours before departure. </p>
